caption:
Armitage Hux, shogun of the First Order.

“Fate is in Heaven, the armor is on the breast, success is with the legs. Go to the battlefield firmly confident of victory, and you will come home with no wounds whatever. Engage in combat fully determined to die and you will be alive; wish to survive in the battle and you will surely meet death. When you leave the house determined not to see it again you will come home safely; when you have any thought of returning you will not return.“


(Who knew his face was so hard to draw ?)

summary: Star Wars and Forces of Destiny: Korkie Kryze Edition
title: Star Wars and Forces of Destiny: Korkie Kryze Edition
body:
okay so guys - I was thinking of various ways Korkie could weave himself into canon as Obi-Wan’s son - ‘cause why not? - and I thought…

He’d look exactly like Obi-Wan Kenobi in his prime. Ginger hair, neat beard. Probably wearing the armor Obi wore during the Lawless arc, has a jetpack, a knife, and a purple lightsaber.

Works with the Rebellion sometimes as a single cell unit

-while running a mission with Han

han: where’d you get the lightsaber, Kryze? stole it from a Jedi?

korkie: from a certain point of view, yes

-walking into Rebel base to take a mission

Korkie: Commander Rex - long time, no see. I like the beard.

Commander Rex: I’ll say the same to you, Prince Kryze - for a moment I thought you were General Kenobi

Korkie, raising his eyebrows: really? interesting.

-when the Rebel Alliance is beginning, shortly after the liberation of Mandalore

Sabine, in the Wren home: why do you use a lightsaber?

Korkie: I consider guns rather uncivilized

-to Luke at some point

luke: you knew Old Ben? What was he like?

Korkie, smiling sadly: He was…*sees Kenobi’s ghost in the background” a good man. Lost his cloaks a bit too often, but a good man.

ghost Obi-Wan: Korkie, no don’t tell him that

-the Rogue Squandron

Probably Wedge: so what really happened on Cato Nemodia? General Tano won’t tell us

Korkie, smirking: oh I can tell you

ghost Obi-Wan: Korkie! 

-or just a simple comic/Forces of Destiny

-someone shows a pic of Korkie as a young man

Rex: that’s not General Kenobi, Commander Skywalker

Luke: what? But I thought-

Rex, putting the pieces together: that’s Prince Korkie - Duchess’ Satine’s nephew…

Han, laughing his ass off nearby: the Empire’s been using that kid’s picture instead of Old Ben? that’s hilarious
